{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/init(_:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/init(light:dark:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/dark","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/light"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/color(for:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/hasForbiddenColorValue()","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/isEqual(_:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleColorSemanticToken","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a color semantic token bgPrimary,","        \/\/ two semantic color tokens will be defined in Figma and generated by tokenator.","        \/\/ They can be declared in protocol ColorSemanticTokens,","        \/\/ and defined automaticaly in OUDSTheme+ColorSemanticTokens extension","        var bgPrimaryLight: ColorSemanticToken { ColorRawTokens.functionalWhite }","        var bgPrimaryDark: ColorSemanticToken { ColorRawTokens.functionalDarkGray880 }","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level color semantic token for bgPrimary","        \/\/ inside ColorMultipleSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+ColorMultipleSemanticToken extension","        var bgPrimary: MultipleColorSemanticToken { MultipleColorSemanticToken(light: bgPrimaryLight, dark: bgPrimaryDark) }","","        \/\/ If the same color is used whatever the color scheme is","        var bgPrimary: MultipleColorSemanticToken { MultipleColorSemanticToken(bgPrimaryLight) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated color semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level color semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["     @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","     @Environment(\\.colorScheme) var colorScheme","","    \/\/ Given you want to apply the color token \"surfaceBrandPrimary\"","    var body: some View {","        \/\/ Apply the token of color for the view without managing yourself the color scheme","        SomeView()","            .oudsBackground(theme.colors.surfaceBrandPrimary)","","        \/\/ Or also oudsForegroundtyle(), oudsForegroundColor(), oudsAccentColor(), ...","    }"]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Or get the token depending to the color scheme and do whatever you want with","    theme.colors.surfaceBrandPrimary.color(for: colorScheme)"]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.8.0","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Since"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/ColorSemanticToken","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" depending to ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"color scheme"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" (i.e. ligh mode or dark mode).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Kind of composite token with multiple values, but not named “composite” because this word is already used in the design system.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens from ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" inside one object.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If a color token exists with its value depending to the color scheme, it must be packed in such ``MultipleColorSemanticToken`","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Tokens for semantics"}],"symbolKind":"class","externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleColorSemanticToken","roleHeading":"Class","role":"symbol","title":"MultipleColorSemanticToken","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleColorSemanticToken","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MultipleColorSemanticToken","kind":"identifier"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplecolorsemantictoken"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(cs)NSObject"],"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(pl)NSObject","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s7CVarArgP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s28CustomDebugStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SQ","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SH","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"kind"